259
00:21:25,905 --> 00:21:27,901
This is an application to join the music club.

260
00:21:27,901 --> 00:21:31,090
I'm the club's president. Think about it.

261
00:21:34,270 --> 00:21:37,241
You can sleep on it if you like.

262
00:21:37,241 --> 00:21:39,313
I'm not rushing to get your answer.

263
00:21:40,806 --> 00:21:44,640
I saw you play the piano,

264
00:21:45,283 --> 00:21:47,613
and you looked really happy.

265
00:22:16,724 --> 00:22:19,439
Did you secretly watch me?

266
00:22:19,439 --> 00:22:21,902
No, I didn't.

267
00:22:21,902 --> 00:22:23,916
I saw you at the Christmas event.

268
00:22:23,916 --> 00:22:26,339
You looked very confident.

269
00:22:30,144 --> 00:22:31,559
One more thing,

270
00:22:31,559 --> 00:22:33,661
I'm the class president.

271
00:22:33,661 --> 00:22:35,931
I need to pay attention to every student,

272
00:22:37,212 --> 00:22:39,252
including you.

273
00:22:40,535 --> 00:22:42,212
You can think about it.

274
00:22:42,212 --> 00:22:48,596
If you have any questions, just give me a call.

275
00:22:49,208 --> 00:22:51,139
I'm leaving now.

276
00:22:53,179 --> 00:22:55,502
Don't skip any of your classes.

277
00:22:55,502 --> 00:22:59,042
Otherwise, the class president will report it.

278
00:23:02,156 --> 00:23:04,353
Bye. See you.

279
00:23:10,510 --> 00:23:12,430
[Music Club Application]

280
00:23:20,456 --> 00:23:22,855
Why is it so hard? I've never hit the target.

281
00:23:22,855 --> 00:23:27,295
Calm down. It takes time to find the focus point.

282
00:23:27,295 --> 00:23:30,676
Before I can find the focus point, I'll probably be shot to death first.

283
00:23:46,461 --> 00:23:50,213
Khun Tanya, this is Palm, my son, the one I told you about.

284
00:23:50,213 --> 00:23:53,513
Palm, this is Khun Tanya, my boss.

285
00:23:53,513 --> 00:23:55,085
Hello.

286
00:23:55,085 --> 00:23:56,636
Hello, Palm.

287
00:23:56,636 --> 00:23:58,534
Palm is in his last year of high school.

288
00:23:58,534 --> 00:24:03,553
I told him to move to Bangkok to prepare for the university entrance exam.

289
00:24:03,553 --> 00:24:08,393
I wanted to ask if he could stay here for two weeks.

290
00:24:08,393 --> 00:24:11,612
When I find a school for him, he will move to the dorm.

291
00:24:11,612 --> 00:24:13,874
Why do you need to do that, Chanon?

292
00:24:13,874 --> 00:24:16,048
There are many empty rooms in the house.

293
00:24:16,048 --> 00:24:18,267
He can stay here with us.

294
00:24:18,267 --> 00:24:22,394
Regarding his school, I think it will be good if he attends the same school as Nuengdiao.

295
00:24:22,394 --> 00:24:27,336
Don't worry. I can talk to the principal about it.

296
00:24:27,336 --> 00:24:29,816
Do you think it's a good idea? I don't want to be a bother to you.

297
00:24:29,816 --> 00:24:31,793
You don't need to feel that way.

298
00:24:31,793 --> 00:24:34,113
You are like a family to me.

299
00:24:34,113 --> 00:24:37,314
You have worked for Piphop for a long time.

300
00:24:38,391 --> 00:24:40,142
Palm,

301
00:24:40,142 --> 00:24:41,899
are there any classes you are interested in?

302
00:24:41,899 --> 00:24:45,445
- Your dad told me that you are good at sports.
-Yes

303
00:24:45,445 --> 00:24:46,748
You are very different from Nuengdiao.

304
00:24:46,748 --> 00:24:49,299
He is not good at sports.

305
00:24:49,299 --> 00:24:51,015
He excels in his academic classes.

306
00:24:51,015 --> 00:24:53,015
Are you talking about me?

307
00:24:54,948 --> 00:24:56,282
No.

308
00:24:56,282 --> 00:25:00,253
Chanon was introducing his son to me.

309
00:25:00,253 --> 00:25:01,314
Khun Nu,

310
00:25:01,314 --> 00:25:03,379
this is my son, Palm.

311
00:25:03,379 --> 00:25:07,273
Palm, this is Khun Nuengdiao, Khun Tanya's son.

312
00:25:08,209 --> 00:25:09,931
Hello.

313
00:25:11,585 --> 00:25:13,319
You should befriend him.

314
00:25:13,319 --> 00:25:16,584
He will be staying with us.

315
00:25:16,584 --> 00:25:19,244
If you have any problems, you can help each other.

316
00:25:44,854 --> 00:25:50,634
[Ben: Are you going to join the music club?]

317
00:25:50,634 --> 00:25:54,654
[Nuengdiao: I'll think about it.]

318
00:25:54,654 --> 00:25:56,484
[Ben: I'm waiting for your answer.]

319
00:27:28,787 --> 00:27:31,053
Why the hell did you do that?

320
00:27:55,203 --> 00:27:56,926
Are you trying to kill me?

321
00:27:56,926 --> 00:27:59,262
I saw you holding the gun.

322
00:27:59,262 --> 00:28:01,833
I was afraid that it might go off accidentally.

323
00:28:01,833 --> 00:28:03,763
I was afraid that you would get hurt.

324
00:28:03,763 --> 00:28:06,024
You are swimming in the middle of the night like that.

325
00:28:06,024 --> 00:28:08,585
Anyone would think that you were a thief!

326
00:28:08,585 --> 00:28:10,670
I'm so sorry.

327
00:28:11,398 --> 00:28:14,245
I was feeling uneasy. I thought everyone was asleep,

328
00:28:14,245 --> 00:28:16,348
so I secretly came to use the pool.

329
00:28:16,348 --> 00:28:20,825
Even if everyone is asleep, it doesn't mean that you can use the pool!

330
00:28:29,936 --> 00:28:35,813
But can you please not tell my dad about me using the pool?

331
00:28:35,813 --> 00:28:38,182
I'm so sorry about this.

332
00:28:38,182 --> 00:28:40,079
I will never use the pool again.

333
00:28:40,079 --> 00:28:44,682
If I don't tell your dad, what do I get in return?

334
00:28:50,682 --> 00:28:53,413
I have nothing to give you.

335
00:28:53,413 --> 00:28:54,784
I have no money.

336
00:28:54,784 --> 00:28:57,348
If there's anything that you want me to do,

337
00:28:57,348 --> 00:28:59,713
I'll do it for you.

338
00:28:59,713 --> 00:29:01,943
I only want one thing from you.

339
00:29:02,779 --> 00:29:05,114
Please, don't tell my dad about this.

340
00:29:13,206 --> 00:29:16,426
Begging me to cover it up doesn't mean you are not guilty.

341
00:29:17,535 --> 00:29:21,438
About the thing that I want you to do, I'll tell you later.

342
00:29:21,438 --> 00:29:23,664
Yes, Khun Nu.

343
00:29:23,664 --> 00:29:26,313
First of all, stop calling me Khun Nu.

344
00:29:26,313 --> 00:29:29,741
I can't do that, you are my boss.

345
00:29:29,741 --> 00:29:32,754
My dad also calls you that.

346
00:29:34,424 --> 00:29:37,241
I'm not surprised that you are Uncle Non's son.

347
00:29:41,141 --> 00:29:44,053
May I?

348
00:29:50,379 --> 00:29:52,273
I removed the magazine from the gun.

349
00:29:52,273 --> 00:29:56,835
If you're going to use the gun, you can put the magazine back in.

350
00:29:56,835 --> 00:29:58,940
It's for your own safety.

351
00:30:13,985 --> 00:30:15,596
Thank you.

352
00:30:35,824 --> 00:30:39,454
Are you ready to go, Khun Nu? Please get in.

353
00:31:03,034 --> 00:31:05,374
[Stop cheating us! Cheater.]

354
00:31:05,374 --> 00:31:06,694
[The market belongs to everyone.]

355
00:31:08,702 --> 00:31:11,592
[Give us back our land.]

356
00:31:33,030 --> 00:31:37,140
[Phoomphiphat Wittayalai High School]

357
00:31:37,144 --> 00:31:40,291
Hello. I'm Pannakorn Jannaloy.

358
00:31:40,291 --> 00:31:42,125
I just transferred to this school.

359
00:31:42,125 --> 00:31:44,522
Okay. Pannakorn, please take a seat.

360
00:31:44,522 --> 00:31:46,694
We are going to begin class now.

361
00:31:46,694 --> 00:31:48,694
In the previous class, we…

362
00:31:48,694 --> 00:31:53,160
He must have good connections. He moved to our school after the semester started.

363
00:31:53,160 --> 00:31:54,902
He even enrolled in this special class.

364
00:31:54,902 --> 00:31:57,188
What family does he belong to? His family name doesn't sound familiar.

365
00:31:57,188 --> 00:31:59,094
Do you recognize his last name?

366
00:31:59,094 --> 00:32:01,785
- No.
- I'll Google it.

367
00:32:01,785 --> 00:32:05,870
Paper, compass, gunpowder,

368
00:32:05,870 --> 00:32:08,590
and printing technology.

369
00:32:08,590 --> 00:32:11,976
I want you to remember these four things.

370
00:32:15,410 --> 00:32:17,054
Nice.

371
00:32:17,054 --> 00:32:18,654
Catch it.

372
00:32:32,898 --> 00:32:36,133
Hey! Do you know how to play basketball?

373
00:32:36,133 --> 00:32:38,736
- Kind of.
- Can you take my position?

374
00:32:38,736 --> 00:32:41,536
My wrist hurts. I don't think I can play anymore.

375
00:32:41,536 --> 00:32:43,242
Is it all right? I don't know anyone on the team.

376
00:32:43,242 --> 00:32:45,922
It's okay. We are all friends here.

377
00:32:45,922 --> 00:32:48,079
Just play the game until it's over.

378
00:32:48,079 --> 00:32:50,982
Ai Tay hired me to play the game. He also opens bets on it.

379
00:32:50,982 --> 00:32:54,003
If I don't finish the game, I will get into trouble with him.

380
00:32:54,003 --> 00:32:56,486
I'm Aun. What's your name?

381
00:32:56,486 --> 00:32:59,758
- Are you a new student?
- Yes. I'm Palm.

382
00:32:59,758 --> 00:33:01,972
Palm, go play for me.

383
00:33:01,972 --> 00:33:03,373
Have fun.

384
00:33:22,542 --> 00:33:24,993
You are good, aren't you?

385
00:33:24,993 --> 00:33:27,575
Not really. I just happened to do well today.

386
00:33:27,575 --> 00:33:30,371
You don't need to be that humble. I can tell that you are good.

387
00:33:30,371 --> 00:33:32,881
How about you join my team?

388
00:33:32,881 --> 00:33:34,962
We can win some money from them.

389
00:33:36,151 --> 00:33:38,335
- Is that a good idea?
- Of course.

390
00:33:38,335 --> 00:33:41,930
We can earn a lot of money, thousands from a single game.

391
00:33:42,658 --> 00:33:45,900
- I'll think about it.
- Okay.

392
00:33:50,900 --> 00:33:54,800
Talk to you later. I have to go now.
- Don't forget my offer.

393
00:34:39,322 --> 00:34:41,234
Why are you following me?

394
00:34:41,234 --> 00:34:42,401
No.

395
00:34:42,401 --> 00:34:45,460
No? You are obviously following me.

396
00:34:45,460 --> 00:34:48,757
Why don't you go play basketball with your friends? You already have friends.

397
00:34:48,757 --> 00:34:51,636
- It's okay.
- If there's nothing, then go away.

398
00:34:52,812 --> 00:34:55,661
You need to tone it down.

399
00:34:55,661 --> 00:34:58,762
If you are teasing Nuengdiao too much, his mother may send a hitman to kill you.

400
00:34:58,762 --> 00:35:00,836
I can't help you with that.

401
00:35:00,836 --> 00:35:04,642
We were just playing around.

402
00:35:04,642 --> 00:35:06,184
You think too much.

403
00:35:06,184 --> 00:35:09,931
He was too sensitive and felt offended by our jokes.

404
00:35:09,931 --> 00:35:11,791
His father died.

405
00:35:11,791 --> 00:35:13,972
Who would be laughing at your jokes?

406
00:35:13,972 --> 00:35:16,707
Did you attend his father's funeral?

407
00:35:16,707 --> 00:35:18,784
Yes. My dad had something to discuss with his mother.

408
00:35:18,784 --> 00:35:20,604
- About what?
- About the land, I guess.

409
00:35:20,604 --> 00:35:24,633
My dad has a land deal with his family.

410
00:35:28,362 --> 00:35:30,654
Don't follow me again!

411
00:35:39,911 --> 00:35:44,067
I'm thinking about visiting Le Cent Hotel Krabi.

412
00:35:44,067 --> 00:35:49,216
It's a low season for tourism. We should focus on cost control and catering services.

413
00:35:49,216 --> 00:35:52,174
It's okay. Everything is under my control.

414
00:35:52,174 --> 00:35:55,302
Why don't you go supervise Le Base Casino on the country's border?

415
00:35:55,302 --> 00:35:58,482
I think you will do well managing that type of business.

416
00:35:58,482 --> 00:36:01,963
P'Ya, you can send anyone to manage the casino.

417
00:36:01,963 --> 00:36:04,085
It's so far away from here, and it's full of gamblers.

418
00:36:04,085 --> 00:36:05,934
Are you kidding me?

419
00:36:07,360 --> 00:36:09,160
Look,

420
00:36:09,165 --> 00:36:12,602
you should give me one of the hotels to manage.

421
00:36:12,602 --> 00:36:15,501
Either a hotel in Krabi, Hua Hin, or Phuket.

422
00:36:15,501 --> 00:36:18,122
This is our family business.

423
00:36:18,122 --> 00:36:20,123
It's not your business.

424
00:36:20,123 --> 00:36:23,337
One more thing, sorry to say this.

425
00:36:23,337 --> 00:36:25,364
You are just an in-law to this family.

426
00:36:25,966 --> 00:36:28,482
You came into this family empty-handed. You can't think everything is yours.

427
00:36:28,482 --> 00:36:29,785
Why isn't it mine?

428
00:36:29,785 --> 00:36:35,253
In your brother's will, he left all the businesses to be under my management.

429
00:36:36,039 --> 00:36:39,213
On behalf of his family.

430
00:36:39,222 --> 00:36:41,713
The businesses will later be passed on to Nuengdiao.

431
00:36:43,794 --> 00:36:48,513
An outsider has no say in the matter.

432
00:36:48,513 --> 00:36:50,313
An outsider?

433
00:36:50,313 --> 00:36:54,013
I think I'm being very kind to you.

434
00:36:55,122 --> 00:36:57,037
Let me remind you again.

435
00:36:57,037 --> 00:37:00,729
I'm not good at managing a casino. You should find someone else to do it.

436
00:37:00,729 --> 00:37:02,949
Then I guess there's nothing else for you to do.

437
00:37:04,522 --> 00:37:06,576
If one day you want to do it,

438
00:37:06,576 --> 00:37:10,388
I hope that you will work harder.

439
00:37:10,388 --> 00:37:14,680
You should learn about the business and show your true potential.

440
00:37:14,680 --> 00:37:17,307
I'll keep an eye on you.

441
00:37:17,307 --> 00:37:21,216
But if you fail to do it, then we can talk about what to do next.

442
00:37:23,027 --> 00:37:24,534
Sure.

443
00:37:25,501 --> 00:37:30,473
Just wait and see who fails first.

444
00:37:35,007 --> 00:37:36,913
Hello, Uncle Kit.

445
00:37:39,864 --> 00:37:41,697
How are you, Nueng?

446
00:37:42,600 --> 00:37:46,600
Chopper told me that you looked a bit stressed at school.

447
00:37:46,600 --> 00:37:50,047
It's nothing. I'm a bit busy with schoolwork.

448
00:37:50,748 --> 00:37:56,596
If there is something bothering you, you can always come and talk to me.

449
00:37:56,596 --> 00:38:00,401
Before your father passed away, he asked me to look after you.

450
00:38:00,401 --> 00:38:01,793
Yes.

451
00:38:04,791 --> 00:38:07,810
Just think of me...

452
00:38:07,810 --> 00:38:10,990
as your second father.

453
00:38:10,993 --> 00:38:14,221
I love you like you are my own child.

454
00:38:14,221 --> 00:38:16,255
Yes. Thank you.

455
00:38:16,255 --> 00:38:22,053
I heard that your father was supposed to give a speech at the Father's Day event at your school.

456
00:38:22,667 --> 00:38:24,042
Yes.

457
00:38:24,848 --> 00:38:29,733
Do you want me to go instead? I can do that.

458
00:38:31,283 --> 00:38:33,523
I need to ask the school first if that is acceptable.

459
00:38:33,523 --> 00:38:35,436
Okay.

460
00:38:35,436 --> 00:38:40,703
Tell me what you want to do. I'm always happy to help you.

461
00:38:53,520 --> 00:38:54,860
[Phoomphiphat Wittayalai High School]

462
00:38:54,862 --> 00:38:56,748
This is the final announcement.

463
00:38:56,748 --> 00:38:59,730
Students whose fathers have arrived,

464
00:38:59,730 --> 00:39:03,240
please take them to register at the auditorium.

465
00:39:03,240 --> 00:39:06,538
The Father's Day event will begin in fifteen minutes.

466
00:39:06,538 --> 00:39:11,563
For students whose father is attending the event, you and your father can take a seat in the front rows.

467
00:39:11,563 --> 00:39:17,039
For students whose fathers cannot attend the event, please take a seat in the back rows.

468
00:39:32,219 --> 00:39:34,093
Khun Nu, where are you going?

469
00:39:36,443 --> 00:39:40,171
Why are you following me here? Are you my servant?

470
00:39:40,171 --> 00:39:41,872
Khun Nu, it's dangerous to sneak out of the school this way.

471
00:39:41,872 --> 00:39:44,351
I think… You call me Khun Nu.

472
00:39:44,351 --> 00:39:45,984
It means that I'm your boss.

473
00:39:45,984 --> 00:39:48,744
Then what right do you have to stop me?

474
00:39:48,744 --> 00:39:51,357
- Khun Nu, please don't be stubborn.
- I'm not being stubborn.

475
00:39:51,357 --> 00:39:53,812
I've been doing this even before I met you.

476
00:39:53,812 --> 00:39:55,486
Why are you annoying me?

477
00:39:55,486 --> 00:39:58,442
Go back inside and don't tell anyone about this.

478
00:40:00,578 --> 00:40:02,326
I don't think you should do it.

479
00:40:02,326 --> 00:40:05,673
If Khun Tanya finds out, you may get in big trouble.

480
00:40:11,184 --> 00:40:13,417
Are you threatening me?

481
00:40:13,417 --> 00:40:16,993
If you don't tell her, she will never know.

482
00:40:18,026 --> 00:40:20,892
If you need to go somewhere, we can go together after school.

483
00:40:20,892 --> 00:40:24,743
No. I'm going right now.

484
00:40:24,743 --> 00:40:30,725
Or should I tell your dad that you secretly used the swimming pool?

485
00:40:30,725 --> 00:40:34,833
I wonder how angry he will be.

486
00:40:49,276 --> 00:40:51,363
Then let me go with you.

487
00:40:51,363 --> 00:40:53,508
I promise I won't tell anyone.

488
00:40:53,508 --> 00:40:56,116
I can't let you go alone.

489
00:40:57,068 --> 00:40:59,558
All right. You can come.

490
00:40:59,558 --> 00:41:01,758
But keep your mouth closed.

491
00:41:10,953 --> 00:41:13,113
Khun Nu, let me climb over first.

492
00:41:13,113 --> 00:41:15,613
I'll catch you on the other side.

493
00:41:18,547 --> 00:41:20,211
Excuse me.

494
00:41:26,233 --> 00:41:29,433
You can climb over. I'll catch you.

495
00:42:57,034 --> 00:42:59,327
Khun Nu, what are we doing here?

496
00:43:36,615 --> 00:43:40,922
My father bought this building during the economic crisis.

497
00:43:40,922 --> 00:43:43,558
He planned to renovate it into high-end condos.

498
00:43:43,558 --> 00:43:46,374
He told me to pick a space on any floor.

499
00:43:46,374 --> 00:43:48,648
He would build a special condo for me,

500
00:43:48,648 --> 00:43:51,136
one unlike any other.

501
00:43:56,003 --> 00:43:58,273
This is the space that I picked.

502
00:43:59,480 --> 00:44:02,337
He promised me here.

503
00:44:02,337 --> 00:44:06,176
He would build the condo for me when I turned eighteen.

504
00:44:07,656 --> 00:44:10,553
He was shot on my birthday.

505
00:44:17,368 --> 00:44:19,928
How do you think I am supposed to feel?

506
00:44:19,928 --> 00:44:22,513
My father died on my birthday

507
00:44:26,584 --> 00:44:29,576
- I'm sorry.
- Is that all you have to say?

508
00:45:10,208 --> 00:45:12,142
Palm,

509
00:45:12,142 --> 00:45:15,453
don't you think it's a bit too coincidental?

510
00:45:17,905 --> 00:45:22,824
Not long after my father was shot, Uncle Non took you into our house.

511
00:45:22,824 --> 00:45:25,653
He said you came to Bangkok to study,

512
00:45:25,653 --> 00:45:28,341
but the semester has already started.

513
00:45:36,618 --> 00:45:39,254
Did my mother bring you here to protect me?

514
00:45:45,738 --> 00:45:47,753
Yes.

515
00:45:47,753 --> 00:45:50,861
My father told me to protect you.

516
00:45:52,656 --> 00:45:55,291
You and I are quite similar.

517
00:45:55,291 --> 00:45:57,308
We are our father's puppets.

518
00:45:57,308 --> 00:45:59,966
We have to do whatever our fathers tell us to do,

519
00:45:59,966 --> 00:46:02,484
be whoever they tell us to be.

520
00:46:03,671 --> 00:46:07,253
We will never get to live the life that we want.

521
00:46:08,621 --> 00:46:12,421
My mom told me that she trusted me and wanted to see me become a leader.

522
00:46:12,421 --> 00:46:16,753
She wanted me to be in charge of everything, but then you are sent to look over me.

523
00:46:17,799 --> 00:46:19,190
Is this what she called trust?

524
00:46:19,190 --> 00:46:23,353
Khun Tanya loves you very much.

525
00:46:23,880 --> 00:46:27,653
She is worried that someone may attack you.

526
00:46:33,553 --> 00:46:35,833
Are you sure you can protect me?

527
00:46:35,833 --> 00:46:38,348
Can you protect me?

528
00:46:38,348 --> 00:46:42,390
A boy from a fisherman's village who only knows about fishing.

529
00:46:42,390 --> 00:46:46,090
Suddenly, you are assigned to protect a wealthy boy.

530
00:46:46,090 --> 00:46:48,241
Are you sure you can do it?

531
00:46:57,588 --> 00:46:59,753
It's my job.

532
00:46:59,753 --> 00:47:02,753
- I'll find a way to do it well.
- I don't need a bodyguard.

533
00:47:02,753 --> 00:47:05,199
I need a friend.

534
00:47:05,199 --> 00:47:07,501
I need someone I can talk to.

535
00:47:07,501 --> 00:47:09,808
I need someone to hang out with me.

536
00:47:09,808 --> 00:47:11,969
You said you will follow my order.

537
00:47:11,969 --> 00:47:14,033
Can you be my friend?

538
00:47:19,795 --> 00:47:24,531
After Piphop died, I always feel uneasy.

539
00:47:25,369 --> 00:47:27,858
I'm worried about Nuengdiao.

540
00:47:27,858 --> 00:47:30,693
I want to find someone to protect him.

541
00:47:31,667 --> 00:47:36,877
Someone who can be with him all the time, when he is at home and school.

542
00:47:36,877 --> 00:47:39,373
Anything can happen to him.

543
00:47:40,176 --> 00:47:42,959
Can you help me, Chanon?

544
00:47:42,959 --> 00:47:45,989
You are the person I trust the most.

545
00:47:50,865 --> 00:47:53,231
Fresh longtail tuna from the sea.

546
00:47:53,231 --> 00:47:55,634
Only 230 baht per kilogram.

547
00:48:01,776 --> 00:48:04,774
Is there something wrong, Dad? Why did you come here?

548
00:48:04,774 --> 00:48:08,136
I'm here to take you to Bangkok. I have a job for you.

549
00:48:08,136 --> 00:48:09,502
What job?

550
00:48:09,502 --> 00:48:11,809
You will be taking care of my boss's son.

551
00:48:11,809 --> 00:48:14,978
Your job will be to protect Khun Nuengdiao.

552
00:48:14,978 --> 00:48:17,520
Don't let anything happen to him.

553
00:48:17,520 --> 00:48:21,119
What about my life here? What about my job and school?

554
00:48:21,119 --> 00:48:24,766
Don't worry about it. I'll take care of everything.

555
00:48:24,766 --> 00:48:26,653
You need to come with me no matter what.

556
00:48:26,653 --> 00:48:30,633
Because I owe that family a lot, and so do you.

557
00:48:30,633 --> 00:48:35,099
Without them, you wouldn't be here today.

558
00:48:38,545 --> 00:48:41,042
Brace yourself for it.

559
00:48:41,042 --> 00:48:45,893
This could be a lifelong job for you.

560
00:48:48,448 --> 00:48:50,048
So?

561
00:48:50,685 --> 00:48:52,739
Can you be my friend?

562
00:48:58,391 --> 00:49:00,293
Of course.

563
00:49:00,293 --> 00:49:02,758
If that's what you want.

564
00:49:04,391 --> 00:49:06,773
I'll be your friend.

565
00:49:30,590 --> 00:49:32,557
I am volunteering to be a piano player here.
